## 6. Official Asset Code Syntax

The standard asset code format is:

`[Family]-[Domain]-[Collection]-[Type]-[Sequence]-[Version]`

### 6.1 Syntax Rules

- `Family` = Layer 1 code
- `Domain` = Layer 2 code
- `Collection` = Layer 3 code
- `Type` = Layer 4 code
- `Sequence` = 3-digit numeric identifier inside that class
- `Version` = semantic version in `vX.Y.Z` format

### 6.2 Example Codes

| Asset | Code |
|---|---|
| Sales cluster manual | LIB-SLS-CLUSTER-MANUAL-001-v1.0.0 |
| Certification student worksheet | CERT-EDU-MODULE-WORKSHEET-004-v1.0.0 |
| Governance naming policy | GOV-COM-INDEX-POLICY-002-v1.0.0 |
| Admin operations prompt set | LIB-ADM-CLUSTER-PROMPT-007-v1.0.0 |
| OPRMT core specification | SPEC-GEN-REPO-SPEC-001-v1.0.0 |

### 6.3 Sequence Assignment Rules

- Sequence numbers are unique inside the same Family + Domain + Collection + Type combination.
- Released codes are never recycled.
- If an asset is split into multiple controlled assets, each new artifact receives a new sequence.
- Sequence changes require library index updates.

