## 11. Version Control Rules

Versioning follows semantic structure:

- `v1.0.0` - first stable controlled release
- `v1.1.0` - non-breaking content expansion or improvement
- `v1.1.1` - minor correction, formatting fix, metadata correction
- `v2.0.0` - major structural or classification-impacting revision

### 11.1 When to Increment Major Versions

Increment the major version when any of the following occur:

- taxonomy structure changes
- required metadata fields change materially
- compatibility with previous index logic is broken
- certification alignment changes
- packaging rules change across the manual

### 11.2 When to Create a New Asset Instead of a New Version

Create a new asset code when:

- the asset serves a different primary use case
- the domain changes
- the artifact type changes
- the asset is split into separately governed deliverables
- the parent collection changes materially

