## 16. Nonconformities

The following conditions are classification nonconformities:

- missing asset code
- missing lifecycle state
- file stored outside canonical path without documented exception
- mismatched code and metadata
- released asset without version control
- duplicate sequence in the same class
- title and code referring to different asset types
- public distribution of draft-classified material without exception approval

### 16.1 Corrective Action Standard

When a nonconformity is found:

1. identify the authoritative record
2. freeze conflicting releases if required
3. correct metadata and storage path
4. update index entries
5. issue version correction or reclassification notice if needed

